	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tokumaru</b> [ Mon Sep 01, 2014 3:50 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Mockups of games from other platforms</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've found that color transitions on the NES look smoother if you change fewer colors each step, instead of the entire palette. As long as *something* changes from one frame to the next, the animation looks continuous. However, most games insist on changing the entire palette at once and not changing anything for several frames until the next complete change, making transitions choppy as hell.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


