		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Video games have routinely carried seizure warnings in the manual for a long time (well before that pokemon episode aired, too). It's part of the standard boilerplate for any GameBoy game, for example. What was different about that Pokemon thing is that it was on a TV show, where there was no such warning or expectation. People with the relevant condition usually know to avoid video games.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


